Once launched, the JVM running Heritrix doesn&#39;t exit unless you tell it 
to, the process dies for other reasons, or the machine restarts.

The general question of how to ensure something is launched at startup 
on a Linux/UNIX system, or relaunched as necessary after problems or on 
a schedule, belongs in other forums -- it&#39;s not a Heritrix-specific 
issue nor inherent to most peoples&#39; use of Heritrix.

- Gordon @ IA

